{"title":"ParálisisFacialPeriférica","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/ParálisisFacialPeriférica iPad.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Parálisis Facial Periférica","guid":"4vud2_yqH4WWUSmI5PCH1Q","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Anatomía del\\NNervio Facial\\N(VII Par)","guid":"sD2SDxlIdZKJX4lSNxcTHQ","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"Nervio MIXTO → motor + parasimpático + sensorial + gustativo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"Segmento\\NIntracraneal","guid":"bGhW34H871S2pueHtU1wHA","children":[{"id":"4","parent":"3","text":"Núcleo facial + núcleo salival superior → tegmento pontino ventral","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"3","text":"Raíz motora + nervus intermedius (raíz visceral mixta)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"3","text":"~10 mm desde tronco encefálico → ángulo pontocerebeloso","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"3","text":"Viaja junto a VIII par (vestibulococlear)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"8","parent":"1","text":"Segmento de Falopio\\N(Canal Facial)","guid":"RSjyRqwpDXz4wL1qffhW9A","children":[{"id":"9","parent":"8","text":"~33 mm de longitud total","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"8","text":"3 segmentos: laberíntico → timpánico → mastoideo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"8","text":"Segmento LABERÍNTICO → MÁS ESTRECHO (0.68 mm)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"12","parent":"11","text":"ZONA DE ESTRANGULAMIENTO → máxima compresión por edema","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"13","parent":"8","text":"Ganglio geniculado → en el genu (segmento laberíntico)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"8","text":"Ramas\\Nintracanaliculares","guid":"OkyYgxtslZkTaA9dk31r9A","children":[{"id":"15","parent":"14","text":"Nervio petroso mayor → glándulas lagrimales y palatinas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"14","text":"Nervio del estapedio → músculo estapedio (amortiguación sonora)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"14","text":"Cuerda del tímpano → gusto 2/3 anteriores\\Nlengua + glándulas\\Nsubmandibular/sublingual","guid":"kiJ42Bmv9xTkQYKAvR2D_w","children":[{"id":"18","parent":"17","text":"Nace ~6 mm sobre foramen estilomastoideo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"17","text":"Cuerpos celulares gustativos en ganglio geniculado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"17","text":"Viajan por nervus intermedius → núcleo tracto solitario","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"21","parent":"1","text":"Segmento\\NExtracraneal","guid":"QZ35DMGgSpBq8Y9YpZcK9w","children":[{"id":"22","parent":"21","text":"Emerge por foramen estilomastoideo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"21","text":"Atraviesa glándula parótida","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"21","text":"Pes anserinus (pata de ganso)\\N→ 5 ramas motoras","guid":"LKilAMqz8JTuEFVYY1jaJg","children":[{"id":"25","parent":"24","text":"Temporal → frente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"24","text":"Cigomática → párpados","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"24","text":"Bucal → mejilla, labios","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"24","text":"Marginal mandibular → labio inferior, mentón","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"24","text":"Cervical → platisma","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"30","parent":"0","text":"Epidemiología","guid":"","children":[{"id":"31","parent":"30","text":"Parálisis de Bell = ~50% de todas las parálisis faciales periféricas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"30","text":"Incidencia: 12-50/100,000 hab/año","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"30","text":"Sin predilección por sexo, raza o geografía","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"30","text":"Riesgo 3x MAYOR en embarazo →\\Nespecialmente 3er trimestre y 1a semana\\Npostparto","guid":"47FJN23SJO7_1Z9KjQGW1A","children":[{"id":"35","parent":"34","text":"Edema perineural + hipercoagulabilidad + inmunosupresión relativa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"34","text":"Asociación con preeclampsia e HTA gestacional","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"37","parent":"30","text":"Diabetes mellitus → 5-10% de los pacientes con Bell","guid":"","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"Microangiopatía de vasa nervorum","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"39","parent":"30","text":"HTA → riesgo modestamente mayor","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"30","text":"Pico de incidencia: 15-45 años","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"30","text":"En ADULTO MAYOR → peor pronóstico de recuperación","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"42","parent":"0","text":"Etiología y\\NPatogénesis","guid":"KFRWblD3ZnQpR4pOSuH-3Q","children":[{"id":"43","parent":"42","text":"Definición → parálisis facial periférica IDIOPÁTICA aislada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"42","text":"Mecanismo → inflamación del nervio facial\\N→ compresión en segmento laberíntico","guid":"LGs959LBICKH-Z0fbiQsHQ","children":[{"id":"45","parent":"44","text":"Perineuro edematoso + infiltrados inflamatorios","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"44","text":"Degeneración de vainas de mielina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"44","text":"Isquemia por compresión de vasa nervorum","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"48","parent":"42","text":"Etiología viral\\N(más aceptada)","guid":"4C04BRFWfI_RsLt6pWpiNw","children":[{"id":"49","parent":"48","text":"HSV-1 → causa\\Nmás frecuente","guid":"NLN2KGezKKVPHZTMhWp4Rw","children":[{"id":"50","parent":"49","text":"PCR positiva en 11/14 pacientes con Bell (fluido endoneural)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"49","text":"PCR negativa en controles","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"52","parent":"48","text":"VZV (Herpes Zóster) → Ramsay Hunt","guid":"","children":[{"id":"53","parent":"52","text":"116/1701 casos de Bell tenían HZ","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"54","parent":"48","text":"Otros: CMV, EBV, adenovirus, rubéola, paperas, influenza, coxsackie, SARS-CoV-2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"48","text":"Rickettsia, Ehrlichiosis (reportes de caso)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"56","parent":"42","text":"Mecanismos no\\Ninfecciosos","guid":"zMFOW0-68FnMC4Qp8pt7Uw","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"Isquemia nocturna → 74% (190/257) notan debilidad al despertar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"56","text":"Diabetes → microangiopatía","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"56","text":"Vacunas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"60","parent":"59","text":"Vacuna intranasal influenza (retirada 2000) → pico 31-60 días post-vacuna","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"59","text":"Vacunas COVID-19 → casos reportados","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"59","text":"RIESGO MENOR con vacuna que con infección por COVID-19","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"63","parent":"56","text":"Predisposición genética → implicada en algunos casos","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"64","parent":"0","text":"Clasificación de\\NHouse-Brackmann","guid":"YRzJna_QqxGaBF3x9tU8SQ","children":[{"id":"65","parent":"64","text":"Grado I → NORMAL → función facial normal en todas las áreas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"64","text":"Grado II →\\NDISFUNCIÓN LEVE","guid":"fOePu56pGs7GYe5YKs6M6Q","children":[{"id":"67","parent":"66","text":"Leve debilidad solo en inspección cercana","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"68","parent":"66","text":"Cierre ocular completo con esfuerzo mínimo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"66","text":"Leve asimetría de sonrisa","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"70","parent":"64","text":"Grado III →\\NDISFUNCIÓN\\NMODERADA","guid":"EEmC6Kb5GcAzREHEeG1cSQ","children":[{"id":"71","parent":"70","text":"Diferencia obvia pero no desfigurante","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"72","parent":"70","text":"Sincinesia notable pero no severa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"73","parent":"70","text":"Cierre ocular completo con esfuerzo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"70","text":"Movimiento de frente leve a moderado","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"75","parent":"64","text":"Grado IV → DISFUNCIÓN\\NMODERADA-SEVERA","guid":"DLbgXBJdp5yH4mkJji2FTQ","children":[{"id":"76","parent":"75","text":"Debilidad obvia y/o asimetría desfigurante","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"75","text":"Sin movimiento de frente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"75","text":"Cierre ocular incompleto","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"75","text":"Sincinesia severa","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"80","parent":"64","text":"Grado V →\\NDISFUNCIÓN SEVERA","guid":"xFZp-VKNoIOJxdYX0JoeWA","children":[{"id":"81","parent":"80","text":"Movimiento apenas perceptible","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"80","text":"Cierre ocular incompleto","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"80","text":"Leve movimiento comisura bucal","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"84","parent":"64","text":"Grado VI → PARÁLISIS TOTAL → sin movimiento","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"64","text":"PRONÓSTICO\\Nsegún grado","guid":"r_OFrrRWJv11SYBq-37ZHg","children":[{"id":"86","parent":"85","text":"HB I-III → recuperación completa muy probable","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"85","text":"HB IV-VI → mayor riesgo de secuelas y sincinesias","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"88","parent":"0","text":"Características\\NClínicas","guid":"byTk7_5JoPewLJuU5kyKuA","children":[{"id":"89","parent":"88","text":"Presentación\\Ntípica","guid":"IwY-_2uyT605gTnUmze7QA","children":[{"id":"90","parent":"89","text":"Inicio SÚBITO en horas (máx 72h)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"89","text":"Parálisis facial UNILATERAL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"89","text":"Deterioro del gusto ipsilateral","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"93","parent":"89","text":"Hiperacusia ipsilateral (n. estapedio)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"89","text":"Disminución del lagrimeo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"89","text":"Pródromo → dolor retroauricular/otalgia","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"96","parent":"88","text":"Patrón de debilidad\\Nfacial PERIFÉRICA","guid":"po9Oldi6xYS6HLdkla5NPA","children":[{"id":"97","parent":"96","text":"Afecta porción SUPERIOR E INFERIOR de hemicara","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"96","text":"Caída de ceja (no puede elevar)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"96","text":"INCAPACIDAD de cerrar ojo → riesgo queratopatía","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"96","text":"Desaparición surco nasolabial","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"101","parent":"96","text":"Caída comisura bucal → desviación hacia lado sano","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"96","text":"Pérdida de control voluntario Y emocional","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"103","parent":"88","text":"Diferenciación CENTRAL\\Nvs PERIFÉRICA","guid":"o8oKoeiuK1ZOLVa8-H8NRg","children":[{"id":"104","parent":"103","text":"PERIFÉRICA (Bell) → toda la hemicara (superior + inferior)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"105","parent":"103","text":"CENTRAL (ACV cortical) → solo porción INFERIOR → RESPETA FRENTE","guid":"","children":[{"id":"106","parent":"105","text":"Inervación corticobulbar BILATERAL al núcleo facial superior","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"107","parent":"103","text":"EXCEPCIONES\\NCRÍTICAS","guid":"Fg2JrCKyYIEuNItd4YdDVw","children":[{"id":"108","parent":"107","text":"ACV PONTINO ventrolateral → mimetiza periférica (afecta núcleo VII)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"109","parent":"107","text":"Lesión distal pes anserinus → puede respetar frente (simula central)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"110","parent":"103","text":"Preservación de control emocional o voluntario → sugiere causa CENTRAL","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"111","parent":"88","text":"Localización\\Nsegún síntomas","guid":"eIqZJdozcfx19fBMc5XvNQ","children":[{"id":"112","parent":"111","text":"Hiperacusia → lesión PROXIMAL a n. estapedio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"111","text":"Pérdida gusto → lesión PROXIMAL a cuerda del tímpano","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"111","text":"Solo paresia facial → lesión DISTAL al foramen estilomastoideo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"115","parent":"88","text":"Temporalidad\\Ndiagnóstica","guid":"iRM1p3B6XPZkRxMpF2CODw","children":[{"id":"116","parent":"115","text":"Inicio en horas a 72h → progresión máx 3 semanas → mejoría en 4 meses","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"115","text":"Inicio SÚBITO con máxima severidad → sospechar ACV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"115","text":"Inicio INSIDIOSO (semanas-meses) → sospechar TUMOR o sarcoidosis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"115","text":"Sin mejoría a 4 meses → re-evaluar diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"120","parent":"0","text":"Evaluación\\NDiagnóstica","guid":"0HXJ9-XJvDSGJ0WCl2Uvvw","children":[{"id":"121","parent":"120","text":"Diagnóstico es CLÍNICO\\N→ criterios","guid":"K_ExDqsreZ9t1FoTgo5jeQ","children":[{"id":"122","parent":"121","text":"Debilidad facial unilateral superior + inferior","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"121","text":"Inicio agudo (1-3 días)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"121","text":"Progresión máximo 3 semanas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"125","parent":"121","text":"Algún grado de recuperación en 4 meses","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"126","parent":"120","text":"Examen\\Nfísico","guid":"DW8ovMZ0ejCi2UK1oBlk6A","children":[{"id":"127","parent":"126","text":"Inspección en reposo → asimetría","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"126","text":"Movimientos → cerrar ojos, elevar cejas, fruncir ceño, mostrar dientes, soplar, platisma","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"129","parent":"126","text":"Gusto → azúcar en mitad anterior lengua (comparativo)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"130","parent":"126","text":"Buscar VESÍCULAS en conducto auditivo externo → Ramsay Hunt","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"126","text":"Palpar PARÓTIDA → masas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"126","text":"Examen neurológico completo → otros pares craneales","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"133","parent":"120","text":"Laboratorio","guid":"","children":[{"id":"134","parent":"133","text":"Serología de Lyme → en zonas endémicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"135","parent":"134","text":"ELISA/IFA → si positivo/equívoco → Western blot","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"136","parent":"133","text":"Glicemia → descartar DM","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"137","parent":"120","text":"Imágenes →\\NNO necesarias\\Nen casos típicos","guid":"AQnKPvWRB3OGSf5abczsBQ","children":[{"id":"138","parent":"137","text":"RM cerebro con gadolinio\\N→ casos atípicos","guid":"3lW3LHLyi3dS_yj1cCli6Q","children":[{"id":"139","parent":"138","text":"Evalúa nervio facial, parótida, causas alternativas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"140","parent":"138","text":"Realce nervio VII en 57-100% de Bell","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"141","parent":"138","text":"AUSENCIA de realce → signo de BUEN PRONÓSTICO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"138","text":"HZ → realce estructuras oído interno","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"143","parent":"137","text":"TC alta resolución → alternativa si RM contraindicada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"137","text":"Repetir imagen a 7 meses si parálisis completa persistente → descartar neoplasia","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"145","parent":"120","text":"Estudios electrodiagnósticos\\N→ para PRONÓSTICO","guid":"GfhvASvcMubWOk5QMsalrw","children":[{"id":"146","parent":"145","text":"VCN (conducción nerviosa)\\N→ día 10+","guid":"VlEr1sdzA-A-O3M3t0797Q","children":[{"id":"147","parent":"146","text":"Compara CMAP lado afectado vs sano","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"148","parent":"146","text":"CMAP <10% normal → degeneración axonal >90% → MAL PRONÓSTICO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"146","text":"Degeneración >98% → resultado muy pobre","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"146","text":"90-98% → recuperación variable, riesgo sincinesias","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"151","parent":"145","text":"EMG →\\Ndía 20-30","guid":"XLuW81UvXqW_HYOv34Wmzw","children":[{"id":"152","parent":"151","text":"Confirma denervación muscular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"153","parent":"151","text":"A 3 meses → buscar reinervación subclínica","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"154","parent":"0","text":"Diagnóstico\\NDiferencial","guid":"I8zt0s12gry-OANHVuzC5g","children":[{"id":"155","parent":"154","text":"Herpes Zóster Ótico\\N(RAMSAY HUNT)","guid":"drzq5pyhjv_uqtaIw_visg","children":[{"id":"156","parent":"155","text":"VESÍCULAS en meato auditivo externo + otalgia severa","guid":"PrzmYsz1C7o0_Ta9vxJf2w","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"155","text":"Zoster sine herpete → sin vesículas, otalgia desproporcionada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"155","text":"PEOR pronóstico que Bell","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"159","parent":"154","text":"Enfermedad\\Nde Lyme","guid":"pmcPrdFduSDZBAzzLZPC0w","children":[{"id":"160","parent":"159","text":"Parálisis facial BILATERAL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"159","text":"Eritema migrans, artralgias, fiebre, cefalea","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"162","parent":"159","text":"Zonas endémicas","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"163","parent":"154","text":"Otitis media / Mastoiditis / Colesteatoma","guid":"","children":[{"id":"164","parent":"163","text":"Diagnóstico por otoscopía","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"165","parent":"154","text":"Síndrome de\\NGradenigo","guid":"vQuJixCmKGrQ3IVIi4JvQA","children":[{"id":"166","parent":"165","text":"VII + VI par (abducens) + dolor retroorbital","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"165","text":"Osteomielitis peñasco temporal","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"168","parent":"154","text":"Síndrome de\\NGuillain-Barré","guid":"PgblrPeN0dijvkrfQESGew","children":[{"id":"169","parent":"168","text":"Parálisis facial BILATERAL SIMÉTRICA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"170","parent":"168","text":"Debilidad progresiva extremidades + arreflexia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"171","parent":"168","text":"Disociación albuminocitológica en LCR","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"172","parent":"154","text":"Sarcoidosis","guid":"","children":[{"id":"173","parent":"172","text":"Parálisis facial uni/bilateral, RECURRENTE","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"174","parent":"172","text":"Otros signos neurosarcoidosis","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"175","parent":"154","text":"Tumores","guid":"","children":[{"id":"176","parent":"175","text":"Curso LENTAMENTE PROGRESIVO (semanas-meses)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"175","text":"TIC o espasmo facial PREVIO → RED FLAG","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"175","text":"Masa parotídea, hipoacusia unilateral","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"175","text":"Sin recuperación >4 meses","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"180","parent":"154","text":"ACV → típicamente respeta frente (central)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"181","parent":"180","text":"ACV PONTINO → puede mimetizar periférica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"182","parent":"154","text":"Síndrome de Melkersson-Rosenthal","guid":"","children":[{"id":"183","parent":"182","text":"Tríada: parálisis facial RECURRENTE + edema facial episódico + lengua fisurada","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"184","parent":"154","text":"Esclerosis múltiple → lesión pontina puede mimetizar Bell","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"185","parent":"0","text":"Tratamiento","guid":"","children":[{"id":"186","parent":"185","text":"CORTICOIDES →\\NPILAR DEL\\NTRATAMIENTO","guid":"kwxL5pQibenrmsTPNCgdyA","children":[{"id":"187","parent":"186","text":"Prednisona 60-80 mg/día x 7 días → taper en 7-14 días","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"186","text":"O Prednisolona 25 mg x2/día x 10 días","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"189","parent":"186","text":"Iniciar DENTRO DE 72h del inicio de síntomas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"190","parent":"186","text":"NNT ~6 para recuperación completa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"191","parent":"186","text":"DOSIS ALTAS (>=80 mg) → posible mayor beneficio (OR 0.17 para no-recuperación a 6m)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"192","parent":"191","text":"Guías japonesas 2023 → recomendación FUERTE para corticoides sistémicos dosis estándar","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"193","parent":"186","text":"En DM → monitorizar glicemia estrechamente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"194","parent":"186","text":"En AM → considerar riesgo hiperglicemia, HTA, retención hídrica, delirium","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"195","parent":"185","text":"ANTIVIRALES →\\NCONTROVERSIA","guid":"44HX1ohJd9GUCmvQnRRrKg","children":[{"id":"196","parent":"195","text":"Valaciclovir 1g c/8h x 7 días O Aciclovir 400 mg x5/día x 10 días","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"195","text":"Evidencia actual → NO beneficio adicional significativo sobre corticoides solos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"198","parent":"195","text":"Guías japonesas 2023 → recomendación DÉBIL para antivirales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"199","parent":"195","text":"Considerar en casos SEVEROS (HB V-VI) → beneficio marginal posible","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"195","text":"OBLIGATORIOS en Ramsay Hunt → Valaciclovir 1g c/8h x 7-10 días","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"201","parent":"185","text":"Protección OCULAR\\N→ CRÍTICO","guid":"ro-gf1virUX9dKLfDWdsYg","children":[{"id":"202","parent":"201","text":"Lágrimas artificiales frecuentes (cada 1-2h)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"203","parent":"201","text":"Ungüento lubricante nocturno","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"204","parent":"201","text":"Oclusión ocular al dormir (parche, cinta adhesiva)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"205","parent":"201","text":"Gafas de protección en exteriores","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"206","parent":"201","text":"Derivar a oftalmología si signos de queratopatía","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"207","parent":"185","text":"Rehabilitación\\Nfacial","guid":"gPJftllP13gAS3l34TwTuQ","children":[{"id":"208","parent":"207","text":"Ejercicios de mímica facial → desde fase aguda","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"209","parent":"207","text":"Biofeedback con espejo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"210","parent":"207","text":"Estimulación neuromuscular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"211","parent":"207","text":"Terapia física → evidencia creciente de beneficio (RS 2024, Varelas et al.)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"212","parent":"207","text":"Masaje facial suave","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"213","parent":"207","text":"EVITAR electroestimulación forzada → riesgo de sincinesias","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"214","parent":"185","text":"Toxina botulínica → para SINCINESIAS residuales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"215","parent":"185","text":"Cirugía de\\Ndescompresión","guid":"G64SVKKnaHt37KCngll8kQ","children":[{"id":"216","parent":"215","text":"Indicación muy selectiva","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"217","parent":"215","text":"CMAP <10% en EDX + parálisis completa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"218","parent":"215","text":"Controversia sobre beneficio real","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"219","parent":"185","text":"Cirugía de REANIMACIÓN facial\\N→ parálisis secuelar permanente","guid":"p8kNOIZ_DCBDowzObJIOcA","children":[{"id":"220","parent":"219","text":"Injerto nervioso (cross-face)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"221","parent":"219","text":"Transferencia de gracilis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"222","parent":"219","text":"Suspensión estática","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"223","parent":"0","text":"Pronóstico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"224","parent":"223","text":"Recuperación COMPLETA\\N→ 70-85% de los casos","guid":"x-qQnTjZuZA45OG_rAWRmQ","children":[{"id":"225","parent":"224","text":"Mayoría inicia mejoría en 3 semanas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"226","parent":"224","text":"Recuperación completa usualmente en 3-6 meses","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"227","parent":"223","text":"Factores de MAL\\NPRONÓSTICO","guid":"FN-hRlabAlZpX60IDrKepQ","children":[{"id":"228","parent":"227","text":"Parálisis COMPLETA (HB V-VI)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"229","parent":"227","text":"Edad >60 años → RELEVANTE EN GERIATRÍA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"230","parent":"227","text":"DM, HTA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"231","parent":"227","text":"Ausencia de recuperación a 3 semanas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"232","parent":"227","text":"CMAP <10% en VCN","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"233","parent":"227","text":"Degeneración axonal >90%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"234","parent":"227","text":"Hiperacusia + ageusia → lesión extensa","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"235","parent":"223","text":"Complicaciones","guid":"","children":[{"id":"236","parent":"235","text":"Sincinesias → movimientos\\Ninvoluntarios asociados (30%)","guid":"YVj0yvThM6QqUE3khBcJsw","children":[{"id":"237","parent":"236","text":"Ojo se cierra al sonreír","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"238","parent":"236","text":"Lagrimeo al masticar (lágrimas de cocodrilo)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"239","parent":"235","text":"Contractura facial","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"240","parent":"235","text":"Queratopatía por exposición → puede causar úlcera corneal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"241","parent":"235","text":"Espasmo hemifacial post-parálisis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"242","parent":"235","text":"Impacto psicológico → ansiedad, depresión, aislamiento social","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"243","parent":"0","text":"Consideraciones\\NGeriátricas","guid":"l6xXfGbCmBZvjiClFsCvlA","children":[{"id":"244","parent":"243","text":"PEOR PRONÓSTICO en >60 años","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"245","parent":"243","text":"Recuperación más lenta e incompleta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"246","parent":"243","text":"Mayor riesgo de DM como factor subyacente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"247","parent":"243","text":"Corticoides →\\Nprecaución con","guid":"uUQ5EDi1y5iZccnC3qjweQ","children":[{"id":"248","parent":"247","text":"Hiperglicemia → monitorizar HGT","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"249","parent":"247","text":"Retención hidrosalina → ICC descompensada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"250","parent":"247","text":"HTA descontrolada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"251","parent":"247","text":"Delirium → especialmente en frágiles","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"252","parent":"247","text":"Osteoporosis → ciclo corto no aumenta significativamente riesgo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"253","parent":"243","text":"Cuidado OCULAR →\\Nespecialmente importante","guid":"ktsxehQmaSd3U5st_NcGyg","children":[{"id":"254","parent":"253","text":"AM con deterioro cognitivo → no reportan síntomas oculares","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"255","parent":"253","text":"Riesgo de úlcera corneal en demencia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"256","parent":"253","text":"Supervisión por cuidador","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"257","parent":"243","text":"Sincinesias → más frecuentes en AM","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"258","parent":"243","text":"DM en AM → degeneración nerviosa facial subclínica previa","guid":"","children":[{"id":"259","parent":"258","text":"Menor reserva neural para recuperación","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"260","parent":"243","text":"Polifarmacia → revisar fármacos que afectan conducción nerviosa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"261","parent":"243","text":"Impacto funcional → dificultad para alimentarse, comunicarse","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"262","parent":"243","text":"RED FLAGS\\Nen AM","guid":"qn3FJsxZw-TssfXJbmdYng","children":[{"id":"263","parent":"262","text":"Parálisis facial nueva → descartar ACV siempre (incluso si parece periférica)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"264","parent":"262","text":"Presentación atípica más frecuente en AM","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"265","parent":"262","text":"Considerar SIEMPRE neuroimagen en AM con parálisis facial nueva","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"266","parent":"0","text":"Perlas\\NClínicas","guid":"J1ZObEeekpcB6x85o6owGg","children":[{"id":"267","parent":"266","text":"Segmento laberíntico (0.68 mm) = zona de estrangulamiento → fisiopatología de Bell","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"268","parent":"266","text":"TIC o espasmo facial PREVIO a debilidad → sospechar TUMOR, no Bell","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"269","parent":"266","text":"ACV pontino puede mimetizar PERFECTAMENTE una parálisis periférica → buscar signos de tronco","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"270","parent":"266","text":"Sin mejoría a 4 meses → NO es Bell → repetir estudio (RM + EDX)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"271","parent":"266","text":"Parálisis bilateral = Lyme o GBS hasta demostrar lo contrario","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"272","parent":"266","text":"Zoster sine herpete → otalgia severa sin vesículas → tratar como Ramsay Hunt","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"273","parent":"266","text":"Corticoides DENTRO de 72h → ventana terapéutica crítica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"274","parent":"266","text":"Antivirales solos NO tienen beneficio → siempre CON corticoides","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"275","parent":"266","text":"Protección ocular desde el PRIMER DÍA → previene complicación más temida (úlcera corneal)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"276","parent":"266","text":"En AM → SIEMPRE neuroimagen ante parálisis facial nueva (umbral bajo para RM)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"277","parent":"266","text":"En AM con DM → recuperación más pobre y sincinesias más frecuentes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"278","parent":"266","text":"Preservación emocional con paresia voluntaria → pensar en causa CENTRAL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"279","parent":"266","text":"CMAP <10% en VCN día 10 → informar pronóstico reservado al paciente","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"280","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"281","parent":"280","text":"1. Ronthal M, Greenstein P. Idiopathic facial nerve palsy (Bell's palsy): Pathogenesis, clinical features, and diagnosis. UpToDate. 2025.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"282","parent":"280","text":"2. Fujiwara T et al. Summary of Japanese clinical practice guidelines for Bell's palsy - 2023 update. Auris Nasus Larynx. 2024;51(5):840-845.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"283","parent":"280","text":"3. Gupta KK et al. Comparing high-dose to standard-dose corticosteroids for Bell's palsy. Otol Neurotol. 2023;44(4):310-316.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"284","parent":"280","text":"4. Stamatiou I et al. Diabetes mellitus and Bell's palsy. Curr Diabetes Rev. 2023;19(1):e080322201913.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"285","parent":"280","text":"5. Varelas EA et al. Physical therapy for idiopathic facial paralysis: A systematic review. Am J Otolaryngol. 2024;46(1):104511.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"286","parent":"280","text":"6. Gardner S et al. Bell's palsy: Description, diagnosis, and current management. Cureus. 2025;17(1):e77656.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"287","parent":"280","text":"7. House JW, Brackmann DE. Facial nerve grading system. Otolaryngol Head Neck Surg. 1985;93(2):146-7.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"288","parent":"280","text":"8. Sullivan FM et al. Early treatment with prednisolone or acyclovir in Bell's palsy. N Engl J Med. 2007;357(16):1598-607.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"289","parent":"280","text":"9. Peitersen E. Bell's palsy: the spontaneous course of 2,500 peripheral facial nerve palsies. Acta Otolaryngol Suppl. 2002;(549):4-30.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":289,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas/General","filename":"ParálisisFacialPeriférica iPad","id":"map_834","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"ParálisisFacialPeriférica iPad"}